    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>LEAFLETTING IN MALLS</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By KAREN DeMASTERS</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Demasters, Karen</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>New Jersey Supreme Court, in case filed by Green Party against Mall at Middle Creek in Secaucus, unanimously rules that political groups and activists have right to reasonable acess to distribute leaflets in shopping malls (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Saying that shopping malls have become the public squares of the modern age, the New Jersey Supreme Court last week unanimously ruled that political groups and activists have a right to reasonable access to  distribute leaflets in them. In a case filed by the Green Party against the Mall at Mill Creek in Secaucus, the court said requiring a $1 million insurance policy, and limiting the group to one day a year in the mall was too restrictive. The court did not say what kind of restrictions would be reasonable.</p>
        <p>KAREN DeMASTERS</p>
      </block>
